edu.ucla.sspace.vector
Interface IntegerVector

All Superinterfaces:
Vector<Integer>
All Known Subinterfaces:
SparseIntegerVector
All Known Implementing Classes:
CompactSparseIntegerVector, DenseIntVector, SparseHashIntegerVector, TernaryVector
public interface IntegerVector
extends Vector<Integer>

An Integer based Vector. Methods which modify the state of a Vector are optional. Implementations that are not modifiable should throw an UnsupportedOperationException if such methods are called. These methods are marked as "optional" in the specification for the interface.

Author:
Keith Stevens

toArray

int[] toArray()
Returns an int array representing this vector. The returned array will be "safe" in that no changes to the array will be reflected in the vector, and likewise for changes to to the vector. The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

Returns:
an int array of this vector.
